- You and Dad.

448
00:39:59.981 --> 00:40:02.067
Yeah.

449
00:40:03.693 --> 00:40:07.864
I am listening, actually. Whoever did it
made sure I was not in the room.

450
00:40:09.616 --> 00:40:12.327
Could you do this? You're better at it.

451
00:40:12.369 --> 00:40:15.497
- There's nothing to worry about.
- Nothing to worry about?

452
00:40:15.580 --> 00:40:20.127
I'm the only Guerin in the phone book.
Who do you think they'll come after next?

453
00:40:20.210 --> 00:40:23.505
Don't flatter yourself, little brother.

454
00:40:23.588 --> 00:40:26.633
Are you going to dance on this
or are you gonna go fast on it?

455
00:40:26.716 --> 00:40:30.679
- Here, give someone else a go.
- Give me a turn!

456
00:41:09.092 --> 00:41:11.511
Are you coming to bed?

457
00:41:12.429 --> 00:41:15.056
- What?
- I know you can hear me. Coming to bed?

458
00:41:15.140 --> 00:41:16.975
I'll be along in a minute.

459
00:41:18.894 --> 00:41:21.605
Fine. Suit yourself.

460
00:41:26.151 --> 00:41:29.905
Turn it down. Turn it down!

461
00:41:31.239 --> 00:41:35.744
Come on. I love it. I love my work.

462
00:41:35.827 --> 00:41:39.372
I'm finally doing something
that can make a difference.

463
00:41:39.456 --> 00:41:42.167
What am I gonna do with you?

464
00:41:42.959 --> 00:41:44.753
- Oh, come on.
- No.

465
00:41:56.806 --> 00:41:59.017
OK.

466
00:42:05.065 --> 00:42:07.150
Come on, man.

467
00:42:08.068 --> 00:42:11.112
Come on. Good boy!

468
00:42:18.161 --> 00:42:20.247
Did we wake you up?

469
00:42:26.086 --> 00:42:31.007
What can I say?
I don't think Gerry Hutch is into drugs.

470
00:42:31.091 --> 00:42:34.302
The Brinks heist, probably.
But drugs is just not his scene.

471
00:42:34.386 --> 00:42:37.639
I understand, but I've been
tracking his movements.

472
00:42:37.722 --> 00:42:41.518
I just need to source the drugs.
The connection's easy. I need your help.

473
00:42:41.643 --> 00:42:46.523
- I need you to stop coming to my office.
- He's got the money.

474
00:42:46.606 --> 00:42:50.235
We're talking about a fella
with no visible source of income

475
00:42:50.318 --> 00:42:53.029
who paid tax on £2 million last year.

476
00:42:53.113 --> 00:42:56.032
It's laundered
through the government's tax amnesty.

477
00:42:56.116 --> 00:43:00.328
- He's got too much money not to be into it.
- In your esteemed journalistic opinion.

478
00:43:00.412 --> 00:43:04.332
I know you seized shipments from Cork.
It's coming from somewhere. Where?

479
00:43:04.416 --> 00:43:08.461
We've impounded drugs from
Liverpool, Scotland, Amsterdam, Pakistan.

480
00:43:08.545 --> 00:43:13.174
You're not the only one trying here, and
Hutch isn't the only one with dirty money.

481
00:43:13.258 --> 00:43:16.261
- Who else you got?
- I could name you a dozen.

482
00:43:16.344 --> 00:43:19.514
Here's the latest candidate,
just in from Interpol.

483
00:43:19.556 --> 00:43:22.183
John Gilligan, one year
out of Portlaoise Prison.

484
00:43:22.267 --> 00:43:24.686
Can you tell me
how this Ballyfermot lowlife

485
00:43:24.769 --> 00:43:29.649
has £300,000 to launder in an Amsterdam
casino? You're the star journalist.

486
00:43:29.733 --> 00:43:31.943
Gilligan. Certainly keeps a low profile.

487
00:43:32.027 --> 00:43:33.194
Yeah?

488
00:43:33.278 --> 00:43:35.905
Hi, Aengus. Yeah, can you hold?

489
00:43:35.989 --> 00:43:37.866
- Can I...?
- Go on. It's a copy.

490
00:43:37.949 --> 00:43:39.909
- Great.
- Just go.

491
00:43:39.993 --> 00:43:42.078
I owe you lunch.

492
00:43:43.747 --> 00:43:46.791
No, run the Brinks story.
Just hold off on the drugs claim.

493
00:43:46.875 --> 00:43:50.337
What for? This stuff you sent is great.

494
00:43:50.420 --> 00:43:53.757
Just give me 24 hours.
I got a tip. This could be big.

495
00:43:53.840 --> 00:43:58.845
- I'm trusting you on this one, Veronica.
- Oh, aren't you great!

496
00:44:09.606 --> 00:44:12.150
Nice tan there, John!

497
00:44:13.860 --> 00:44:16.237
Hope there's no hard feelings between us.

498
00:44:16.321 --> 00:44:22.035
I'm not one to take a bullet
through my window personally.

499
00:44:22.118 --> 00:44:24.537
Get lost.

500
00:44:24.621 --> 00:44:27.749
I told you to be careful
with the likes of Gerry Hutch.

501
00:44:27.832 --> 00:44:32.337
But you didn't tell me
about a fella named Gilligan.

502
00:44:32.420 --> 00:44:33.421
Who?

503
00:44:33.505 --> 00:44:36.341
You provided him with a car
when he got out of prison.

504
00:44:36.424 --> 00:44:39.052
John Gilligan. Do you want me to spell it?

505
00:44:39.135 --> 00:44:42.639
I run a bleedin' garage.
I provide loads of cars to people.

506
00:44:42.722 --> 00:44:45.600
Hardly gonna remember
every one of them, now, am I?

507
00:44:45.642 --> 00:44:50.355
- Is that him there?
- Why should I give a shite?

508
00:44:50.438 --> 00:44:55.568
No reason, really. Just the fella behind
the security guard looks a lot like you.

509
00:44:56.945 --> 00:45:00.532
- Now, there's a coincidence.
- Where's his money coming from?

510
00:45:00.615 --> 00:45:02.992
Is he providing
hash and heroin to Mitchell?

511
00:45:03.076 --> 00:45:06.621
I can't help you, Veronica.
Don't know nothing about him.

512
00:45:06.663 --> 00:45:09.624
If I hear of anything,
I'll let you know, OK? Molly!

513
00:45:09.666 --> 00:45:13.878
You can keep the photo if you like.
It's a nice one of you. We got plenty.

514
00:45:18.675 --> 00:45:21.761
- You sell horses yourself?
- I do.

515
00:45:21.845 --> 00:45:26.141
- You have a number.
- I sell them on to Germany mostly.

516
00:45:26.224 --> 00:45:30.019
Myself and Geraldine are planning
to make this the largest and finest

517
00:45:30.103 --> 00:45:34.023
equestrian centre in all of Ireland.

518
00:45:34.107 --> 00:45:37.444
Well, I must say the size is impressive.

519
00:45:37.527 --> 00:45:39.404
Said the nun to the sailor.

520
00:45:40.613 --> 00:45:46.536
How about an aperitif?
Some champers, caviar? It's all imported.

521
00:45:46.619 --> 00:45:49.914
John and I have great plans for this place.

522
00:45:49.998 --> 00:45:52.083
Hang on.

523
00:45:53.418 --> 00:45:55.503
Hello?

524
00:45:55.587 --> 00:45:56.880
- Hello?
- John...

525
00:45:56.963 --> 00:46:00.467
You're breaking up there. Hello?

526
00:46:00.550 --> 00:46:02.594
- It's Traynor.
- Johnny.

527
00:46:02.677 --> 00:46:07.015
Listen, Veronica Guerin's got hold of
a photo of us in Amsterdam.

528
00:46:07.098 --> 00:46:13.521
But, John, I swear I had nothing
to do with it. I never mentioned your name.

529
00:46:13.605 --> 00:46:15.690
But she was asking about you.

530
00:46:15.732 --> 00:46:21.988
Johnny, I told you before, if she so much
as mentions my fucking name, you pay.

531
00:46:25.158 --> 00:46:27.452
Fucking eejits!

532
00:46:27.535 --> 00:46:29.621
Fuck 'em!

533
00:46:34.918 --> 00:46:37.003
Happy Christmas!

534
00:46:39.714 --> 00:46:42.592
- Now, isn't this great?
- When's Mum coming here?

535
00:46:42.675 --> 00:46:46.471
She'll be here soon.
We'll want something stronger than that.

536
00:46:51.601 --> 00:46:54.062
Yeah? Ma, how are you?

537
00:46:54.145 --> 00:46:57.482
- Happy Christmas, Ann. You look great.
- Happy Christmas.

538
00:46:57.565 --> 00:47:01.444
- Where's your mum?
- You know her. Always going for the gold.

539
00:47:02.362 --> 00:47:04.280
All right.

540
00:47:05.490 --> 00:47:07.242
There's someone at the door, Ma.

541
00:47:07.325 --> 00:47:10.870
My phone'll be on all night.
You can call me whenever you want.

542
00:47:10.954 --> 00:47:14.082
I love you too. OK. Bye. Bye.

543
00:47:21.756 --> 00:47:24.133
Yeah, all right, all right.

544
00:48:32.327 --> 00:48:34.829
Veronica's been shot!

545
00:48:40.877 --> 00:48:41.878
How are you?

546
00:48:42.003 --> 00:48:44.297
- How are you?
- You look gorgeous.

547
00:48:44.380 --> 00:48:48.009
- Look at you. For God's sake.
- Hey, Willy.

548
00:48:49.469 --> 00:48:52.347
Can't find any sport on.
Can you believe it?

549
00:48:52.430 --> 00:48:56.309
...extensive investigations
into organised crime in Dublin...

550
00:48:56.392 --> 00:48:59.979
Why do they always use
that brutal picture?

551
00:49:00.063 --> 00:49:01.898
It was a very serious incident.

552
00:49:01.981 --> 00:49:05.902
Veronica Guerin
is a very talented journalist.

553
00:49:06.027 --> 00:49:10.073
An attack like this could be seen
as an attempt to muzzle her

554
00:49:10.156 --> 00:49:15.119
because of certain publications
or articles she wrote.

555
00:49:15.203 --> 00:49:18.539
This would be connected
with last month's £3 million robbery?

556
00:49:18.623 --> 00:49:22.251
We all know who pulled that one,
don't we, Hutch? He threatened me.

557
00:49:22.335 --> 00:49:26.047
Veronica, please, stop this.
Write about fashion, about football.

558
00:49:26.130 --> 00:49:30.259
Write about anything you like, but stop this.
You don't have to do it any more.

559
00:49:30.343 --> 00:49:35.473
I don't see myself covering the catwalks
or doing a gardening column, Aengus.

560
00:49:35.556 --> 00:49:38.601
You've always wanted
to write about politics.

561
00:49:38.685 --> 00:49:40.937
I am. Drugs are political.

562
00:49:41.062 --> 00:49:44.023
What if I told you
I wouldn't publish your stuff any more?

563
00:49:44.107 --> 00:49:45.942
But you never would tell me that.

564
00:49:46.067 --> 00:49:48.903
For Christ's sake,
there's no sport channel.

565
00:49:48.945 --> 00:49:51.739
- We have to go.
- What kind of hospital is this?

566
00:49:51.823 --> 00:49:54.409
Is this what we pay health insurance for?

567
00:49:54.492 --> 00:49:57.286
- Where Cathal?
- He's at your sister's with your mum.

568
00:49:57.370 --> 00:49:59.288
- Don't worry.
- I'm not worried.

569
00:50:00.248 --> 00:50:03.042
Right. We've just got you
24-hour police protection.

570
00:50:03.126 --> 00:50:05.211
- OK?
- Grand.

571
00:50:06.295 --> 00:50:11.050
What a way to spend Christmas Eve,
looking at the poxy box.

572
00:50:11.134 --> 00:50:13.970
Mary Poppins. Gone with the Wind.

573
00:50:14.053 --> 00:50:17.849
Next thing you know
it'll be A Wonderful fucking Life.

574
00:50:17.932 --> 00:50:20.685
The doctor says it missed
the artery and the bone.

575
00:50:20.768 --> 00:50:25.189
Point-blank range with a.45,
and this is all they could do.

576
00:50:25.273 --> 00:50:27.859
- Where's Cathal? How is he?
- He's fine.

577
00:50:27.942 --> 00:50:31.070
Where is he? Oh, yeah. He's with Mum.

578
00:50:31.154 --> 00:50:34.198
- Yeah. He keeps asking for you.
- Yeah?

579
00:50:36.075 --> 00:50:39.746
...shooting happened shortly after...
...investigations for the...

580
00:50:39.829 --> 00:50:42.498
...warning from a crime gang.

581
00:50:44.959 --> 00:50:47.003
You gonna stop this now?

582
00:51:02.977 --> 00:51:05.271
Nan, look! It's Mum!

583
00:51:21.788 --> 00:51:24.957
- Give me the keys.
- I know what I'm doing, Graham.

584
00:51:25.041 --> 00:51:29.378
- They shot me cos I'm on the right track.
- Give me the keys, please.

585
00:51:29.462 --> 00:51:32.131
- Thank you.
- Would you give me the keys?

586
00:51:32.215 --> 00:51:34.050
No.

587
00:51:34.133 --> 00:51:36.636
Look at the state of you.

588
00:51:38.471 --> 00:51:41.140
Do you think I want to do this, do you?

589
00:51:41.224 --> 00:51:44.310
I don't want to do it. I have to do it.

590
00:51:44.393 --> 00:51:48.272
You're a journalist. You write.
You let the Gards look after this.

591
00:51:48.356 --> 00:51:52.652
Oh, Graham, come off it. The Gards can't
do anything. They'll get away with it.

592
00:51:52.735 --> 00:51:55.196
- 14 shootings in 14 months.
- You're one of them.

593
00:51:55.279 --> 00:51:58.199
I know who the guys are.
Would you just give me the keys?

594
00:51:58.282 --> 00:52:01.327
No. Tough shit.

595
00:52:01.410 --> 00:52:04.080
Come on inside. Please.

596
00:52:04.205 --> 00:52:07.792
They're not getting away with it.
I'll catch a cab, then.

597
00:52:07.875 --> 00:52:09.961
Oh, for God's sake.

598
00:52:12.046 --> 00:52:14.090
Ah, Jesus Christ.

599
00:52:15.091 --> 00:52:17.718
Yeah, hi. It's Veronica Guerin.
I'd like a...

600
00:52:17.802 --> 00:52:20.847
Thank you. Come on. Get in.

601
00:52:21.848 --> 00:52:24.767
- Who's driving?
- You can't drive with two good legs.

602
00:52:24.851 --> 00:52:28.187
- You think I'll let you drive with one?
- That's low, that is.

603
00:52:28.271 --> 00:52:33.442
- You drive like an old granny.
- Come on, Hopalong, get in.

604
00:52:34.318 --> 00:52:37.822
Where is she going? She only got out
the hospital a couple of days ago.

605
00:52:37.905 --> 00:52:39.991
I know.

606
00:52:49.709 --> 00:52:51.794
You let me do it.

607
00:52:58.551 --> 00:53:03.139
Look! Veronica Guerin.
Come here. Have a look.

608
00:53:03.264 --> 00:53:05.349
Tommy Mullen?

609
00:53:19.864 --> 00:53:21.657
Fatso Mitchell?

610
00:53:22.617 --> 00:53:25.119
- Yeah.
- This is for you.

611
00:53:29.957 --> 00:53:32.043
Get the fuck out of here. Here!

612
00:53:35.588 --> 00:53:40.301
- Your column's upsetting me mother.
- Ah, you poor fella.

613
00:53:40.384 --> 00:53:45.431
You think I'm a drug dealer, don't you?
Well, I'm no drug dealer.

614
00:53:45.514 --> 00:53:50.394
I've seen family and friends dying
week in, week out because of 'em.

615
00:53:50.478 --> 00:53:53.856
All right. Why did you shoot me?

616
00:53:56.484 --> 00:54:01.155
No, I had nothing to do with shooting you.
I wouldn't have missed.

617
00:54:08.955 --> 00:54:11.916
I'm telling you, he isn't here.

618
00:54:11.999 --> 00:54:15.044
And I have to go. I'm busy.

619
00:54:15.127 --> 00:54:17.964
- How old are you?
- None of your business.

620
00:54:18.047 --> 00:54:21.175
Please, just give this to Traynor.

621
00:54:22.510 --> 00:54:25.471
Are you gonna be OK?
I mean, your leg and all?

622
00:54:25.554 --> 00:54:27.890
Yeah, I'm grand.

623
00:54:28.683 --> 00:54:31.060
Are you gonna be all right?

624
00:54:35.940 --> 00:54:40.695
And I thought... I mean, I've always
believed that... Well, I'm a journalist.

625
00:54:40.778 --> 00:54:45.783
Nobody shoots the messenger.
I mean, a journalist doesn't get shot.

626
00:54:45.866 --> 00:54:50.329
If the bullet had hit an artery,
you could have died.

627
00:54:50.413 --> 00:54:53.207
So why do you do it?
Why do you take the risks?

628
00:54:53.249 --> 00:54:59.964
Well, I'll give her this. It takes some balls
to shoot yourself in the leg for publicity.

629
00:55:00.047 --> 00:55:03.634
- She should have shot herself in the balls.
- Bigger target.

630
00:55:03.718 --> 00:55:08.222
- Shall we?
- Never liked this place anyway.

631
00:55:08.264 --> 00:55:14.020
She can always use the insurance money
for a course in journalism.

632
00:55:28.951 --> 00:55:31.746
Here. Check this out.

633
00:55:31.829 --> 00:55:35.583
...bringing to the attention
of the public generally

634
00:55:35.666 --> 00:55:40.921
a culture that exists in our society
that nobody knows anything about.

635
00:55:41.005 --> 00:55:43.924
Your girlfriend's looking
very fucking healthy.

636
00:55:44.008 --> 00:55:46.385
Too bad the moron you hired
shot her in the leg.

637
00:55:46.469 --> 00:55:50.014
Now the whole country's watching her,
thanks to you.

638
00:55:50.097 --> 00:55:53.809
She's a real martyr, thanks to you, Coach.

639
00:55:53.893 --> 00:55:56.937
Saint Veronica of the Sunday Independent.

640
00:55:57.021 --> 00:56:02.526
Relax, will you? She's convinced
it was Gerry Hutch that done it.

641
00:56:02.610 --> 00:56:05.321
You better pray she stays that way.

642
00:56:05.404 --> 00:56:07.615
Come on.

643
00:56:07.698 --> 00:56:10.159
Champagne - now.

644
00:56:10.242 --> 00:56:14.538
These letters that you delivered.
What did you say in them?

645
00:56:14.622 --> 00:56:17.333
There was one simple question
on each of the letters,

646
00:56:17.416 --> 00:56:21.587
and it was
"Were you responsible for my attack?"

647
00:56:33.140 --> 00:56:35.226
Mr Gregory?

648
00:56:35.309 --> 00:56:39.355
What are you doing here? How did you get
past Security? You can't just barge in.

649
00:56:39.480 --> 00:56:42.483
I'm sorry. Do you mind if I sit down?

650
00:56:43.317 --> 00:56:48.489
A young woman wounded, on a crutch.
I'd be at a disadvantage. Take a seat.

651
00:56:48.572 --> 00:56:51.992
I've come to apologise,
if I've got it all wrong.

652
00:56:52.076 --> 00:56:55.621
All of you journalists have got it wrong.

653
00:56:56.372 --> 00:56:59.083
You call these guys the Viper,
the Monk, the General.

654
00:56:59.166 --> 00:57:01.502
You glorify them. They're not movie stars.

655
00:57:01.585 --> 00:57:04.296
With respect, I've no option.

656
00:57:04.380 --> 00:57:07.716
I can't name them.
Your libel laws won't let me.

657
00:57:07.800 --> 00:57:10.469
Journalists are going to jail
for doing their job.

658
00:57:10.553 --> 00:57:14.390
Liz Allen, she's facing imprisonment
for exposing these murderers.

659
00:57:14.473 --> 00:57:17.309
I'm not getting involved
in your personal vendettas.

660
00:57:17.393 --> 00:57:21.105
- I'm not here because I was shot.
- Now we know what you're not here for.

661
00:57:21.188 --> 00:57:26.944
Look, I've been writing quite extensively,
in a balanced way, for the past 18 months.

662
00:57:27.027 --> 00:57:32.491
You must have missed some of my articles.
On June 11th - I just want to clarify this -

663
00:57:32.575 --> 00:57:36.203
I suggested extending
detention periods for drug offenders.

664
00:57:36.287 --> 00:57:40.499
Then on July 16th I wrote about tax
officials - I mean, this is ridiculous -

665
00:57:40.583 --> 00:57:43.544
saying that they are paid
only to record declared income,

666
00:57:43.627 --> 00:57:46.422
not to worry about
whether it comes from drugs.

667
00:57:46.505 --> 00:57:49.216
Then on July 23rd
I wrote about the gardai.

668
00:57:49.300 --> 00:57:54.138
They can seize drug proceeds but can't
hold them. How frustrating is that?

669
00:57:54.221 --> 00:57:58.517
I don't need you to tell me the fight against
drugs has been hampered, crippled,

670
00:57:58.601 --> 00:58:01.270
by the laws that we have at the moment.

671
00:58:01.353 --> 00:58:05.691
- We're on the same side, Mr Gregory.
- We're on the same side?

672
00:58:05.774 --> 00:58:09.778
I don't like your methods,
and I do not like your paper.

673
00:58:09.862 --> 00:58:14.450
Yeah. It's a rag. But it's a popular rag.

674
00:58:14.533 --> 00:58:17.286
Use it. Get your message out. Use me.

675
00:58:17.369 --> 00:58:20.456
You've got to change these laws
that favour the criminals.

676
00:58:20.581 --> 00:58:24.460
